review_blob: One of my favorite mass market beers, a very good heavy beer that fills you up.  Smells like a mans beer, looks like a mans beer, not for those worried about drinking something with the consistescy of oil
Decent beer with abover average flavor.  Would be better if it were a little heavier

terrible beer for the masses.  One who drinks this beer cares not about the taste but about getting trashed, very very slowly.  Comparable to cough syrup in taste, that is to say nasty, but at least cough syrup will cure your cold.  When given a choice, opt for cough syrup, you obviously dont care about taste anyways.

This is a good solid beer that can somethmes be a little watery.  It has an average amount of bitterness, but not overpowering.  The only thing lacking in this beer is that it may be a little to light.
beer_name: James Page Iron Range Amber Lager
